narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a basic history of Egypt and Mesopotamia and how the development of writing shaped the two cultures.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Handling actual artifacts Interesting subject matter Weaknesses: Would have liked there to be more discussion time. I think the lectures took up too much of class time and if they were broken up with periodic discussions the class would have been more engaging.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. It's a great little class that lets you explore the Babylonian collection as you learn about writing.
If you want to handle real artifacts you should definitely take this course.
